features: GLOWS IN THE DARK: These pacifiers for baby have a glow in the dark functionality, making it easy for you to locate quickly at night without any stumbling and searching, helping your baby sleep better.
VENTILATED & COMFORTABLE SHIELD: These orthodontic pacifiers for babies have a curved sterilizing shield with openings to prevent moisture build-up and allow baby’s skin to breathe.
FLEXIBLE SHAPE FOR 16+ MONTH BABY : The SkinSoft nipple on these pacifiers is 60% thinner and 4x more flexible than average, exerting less pressure on the mouth in order to avoid jaw deformations.
SELF - STERILIZING CASE: Add water and pop into the microwave to sterilize MAM silicone pacifiers 16+ months in just 3 minutes and store in case for at home and travel to protect the pacifiers.
HIGH QUALITY: Approved by 94% of babies*, our 100% BPA & BPS free orthodontic silicone pacifiers meet or exceed US safety standards and are extremely durable, while being soft and flexible.
body.description: No more frustration trying to find your lost pacifiers at night! This pacifier glows in the dark, making it easy for baby and parent to find in the evening hours. Specially designed with your little one’s teeth and jaw in mind, the MAM Perfect Pacifier is clinically proven* to reduce the risk of open bite and increased overbite later in life. With a 60% thinner neck and 4 times more flexible nipple** than a regular pacifier, you can be assured that your little one’s favorite binky is safe for their development as it puts less pressure on their jaw and teeth. MAM’s medically engineered nipples feature life-like, SkinSoft textured silicone that feels more natural, just like mom. With multiple nipple and shield sizes to pick from, MAM nipples are easily accepted by babies of all ages, with 94% nipple acceptance among babies tested***. Babies simply love the ease and comfort of latching onto MAM nipples. Sterilize baby’s MAM pacifier in the microwave using the convenient MAM self-sterilizing storage case. Pacifiers kept in the closed box will remain disinfected for up to 48 hours: Fill pacifier case with water. Place pacifier in the pacifier case with the nipple facing down. Follow pacifier package instructions for microwave setting. Cool completely before use. *Y. Wagner, R. Heinrich-Weltzien, “Effect of a thinneck pacifier on primary dentition: a randomized controlled trial”, Orthodontics & Craniofacial Research, Volume 19, Issue 3, pages 127–136, August 2016. **Scientific reports from Wild Hi-Precision institute verify: the MAM Perfect’s teat neck is on average 60% thinner; test series by the University Clinic of Dentistry Vienna confirm: it is also on average 4 times more flexible than comparable pacifiers. (Between: 32% – 83% thinner / 1.1 – 19.5 times more flexible than regular silicone pacifiers). *** Market Research 2009-2017, tested with 1,508 babies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Flexible and strong
reviews.reviewText: My son has always used Mam pacifiers at night because of the glow in the dark feature, which lasts hours. He can find it all night, which is a life saver. He didn’t seem to notice when we switched to these. They’re sturdy at the base, but still flexible. The base isn’t hollow except for a tiny channel, which lets the nipple still be squishy.I saw some reviews on toddler pacifiers where they say their toddler was able to bite through them. I feel like it would take a lot for that to happen with these, unless your toddler was especially bitey, in which case I wouldn’t trust any pacifier.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect pacifier is a different style than the original
reviews.reviewText: It seems like the people leaving negative reviews of the slim base of this pacifier are not looking at the images or description on how this style (“Perfect”) is different from the original style.My 4 year old used the original style for the first 18 months of his life and has no bite or teeth issues.My now 18 month old has used this brand in the updated Perfect style from birth. The only differences I can attest to are these:1. They indeed do not come with the blue security tag in the case. However the tag was pretty stringy and did not seem to have much substance to begin with, so I don’t know how secure it actually was in showing the case hadn’t been previously opened. I make sure the seller I purchase these from is Amazon, and it may be naive on my part, but I feel a little less worried in that regard.2. These are easier to bite through than the original. My daughter has bitten through most of them within 2 months of use. So check them often to avoid a potential choking accident.That being said, I do prefer this style as it would seem to have less impact on oral development than the original.The glow in the dark doesn’t do too much for me. I almost prefer a dark color, as it has more contrast against a white sheet than the glow in the dark and is therefore easier to spot in the middle of the night in my opinion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fixed my toddler’s teeth!
reviews.reviewText: My 18 month old was starting to get curved teeth from using her pacifier. We only use pacifiers for nap time and night time. I switched to these orthodontic pacifiers and her teeth have straightened up within less than one week. They are durable and glow in the dark very well. They also fit onto her existing elephant pacifier holder which is a huge bonus!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2021

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great pacis, not the design I ordered
reviews.reviewText: These are the best pacifiers out there. My daughter loves them. The glow in the dark feature is a must-have so she can easily find them in the middle of the night. They are also orthodontist approved. Don't expect to get the design you thought you ordered, though. This is the second time I received a pack completely different than the ones pictured. But I can overlook this, as we are always needing replacements for ones she loses!
